parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Loose Steering and Power Steering Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power steering system can cause the steering wheel to become loose, making it difficult to control the vehicle, which can lead to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The steering wheel feels loose or sloppy
the steering wheel has excessive play
the vehicle pulls to one side
the steering wheel does not respond to input
the vehicle is difficult to steer
the power steering warning light illuminates.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Water Ingress into OnStar, Navigation, and Compass System
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Water ingress into the OnStar, navigation, and compass system can cause malfunction or failure of these systems, leading to loss of critical safety features and navigation capabilities.
symptoms: Water accumulation in the shark fin antenna
malfunction or failure of OnStar
navigation
and compass systems.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Rear Window Slider Smoking and Shattering
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The rear window slider smoking and shattering can cause injury to occupants, especially children, and create a hazardous driving condition.
symptoms: Smoke emanating from the rear window slider
loud bang
and shattering of the rear passenger side window.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The intermittent "Service Trailer Brake System" warning can cause loss of trailer braking functionality, leading to increased stopping distances and potential accidents.
symptoms: Intermittent "Service Trailer Brake System" warning
loss of trailer braking functionality
warning may occur when towing or not towing.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The electrical system failure can cause multiple warning lights to illuminate, including ABS, stability control, and airbag lights, and potentially lead to loss of vehicle control and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: Multiple warning lights illuminating
vehicle shutdown
restart issues
and loss of vehicle control.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The 7-way trailer plug issues can cause loss of trailer lighting and braking functionality, leading to increased stopping distances and potential accidents.
symptoms: Trailer plug coming loose during normal driving conditions
loss of trailer lighting and braking functionality
and sagging of the plug due to upside-down flap configuration.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the CP4 fuel pump can cause the engine to stall, leading to loss of power steering and brakes, which can result in accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle lurches
makes a noise
and goes into reduced power mode
eventually shutting off; the engine will not restart; the fuel filter indicator shows 0% and the vehicle goes into low power mode.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A faulty crankshaft can cause irreparable damage to the engine, leading to costly repairs and potential safety hazards.
symptoms: Engine failure
stalling
or damage to the engine.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The engine stalling without warning can cause loss of control, accidents, or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls without warning at any rate of speed
multiple times.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the turbo and oil cooler can cause oil leaks, engine damage, and potentially lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Oil leak
turbo failure
oil cooler failure
engine damage.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the trailer brake system can cause the brakes to malfunction, leading to reduced stopping power, increased stopping distance, and potential accidents.
symptoms: The "service trailer brake system" warning appears on the dashboard
the brakes make a noise when applied
the brakes do not seem to stop the vehicle properly
a ticking noise comes from the engine or brakes.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The brake noise and performance issues can cause reduced confidence in the vehicle's braking ability, leading to increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: A loud squealing noise is heard when the brake pedal is depressed
the brakes make a noise when applied
the brake pedal is difficult to depress
the brakes fail to operate without warning
extra force is required to depress the brake pedal.
